RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Localism
<hw>Lo"cal*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
state or quality of being local; affection for a particular
place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A method of speaking or acting peculiar to a certain
district; a local idiom or phrase.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Locality</ent>⟦br⟧
